# Branch naming

Format: <type>/ALE-<NNN>-<short-slug>

- type: one of feat, fix, docs, chore, spike, refactor, test, ci
- ALE-NNN: the Linear ticket ID this branch implements — required, exact case (e.g. ALE-125)
- short-slug: 3-6 words, kebab-case, derived from the Linear ticket title

Rules:
- Never create a branch without a known ALE-NNN ticket ID. If none is given, ask rather than guessing or omitting it.
- Use "docs/" for ADR-landing / documentation tickets, even if the diff touches code.
- Use "ci/" for GitHub Actions, workflow, and other CI/CD pipeline changes.
- Use "feat/" or "fix/" for implementation tickets.
- One branch per ticket — do not combine frontend and backend work from separate tickets into one branch.
- All lowercase, hyphen-separated, no underscores, no spaces.

Examples:
- feat/ALE-126-deploy-render-cloudflare
- ci/ALE-137-gate-render-deploy-behind-testyml
- docs/ALE-125-adr-0013-deployment-doc
- feat/ALE-121-frontend-auth-lock-modal
